This project implements a House Price Prediction system using Machine Learning techniques, specifically Multiple Linear Regression and Support Vector Machine (SVM) algorithms. Due to the absence of a real-world dataset, a synthetic dataset was generated programmatically using NumPy to simulate housing attributes such as area, number of bedrooms, bathrooms, property age, and location. The data was preprocessed through feature encoding and standardization to improve model performance. Multiple Linear Regression was used to model the relationship between independent variables and house prices, while SVM was explored for predictive analysis and comparison. Model evaluation was performed using metrics such as R² Score, Mean Absolute Error (MAE), and Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE). The project demonstrates the end-to-end machine learning workflow, including data generation, preprocessing, training, prediction, and performance assessment.
